{
  "stem": "1550.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We saw the port and Mount Carmel in the distance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody was singing the Hatikvah on deck.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a great moment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I can assure you that nobody who on that ship will-- [CRYING] Anyway, so we arrived in Haifa, and-- and the British police came on board and they said, well, the other two ships had arrived.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the problem is there is no-- no place on land.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you have to go to another ship, but you'll be very comfortable there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now usually, what the British had done in the past, what they had done was they-- people were-- with illegal immigrants, that is to say-- they put them into a camp and then-- then they let them go, but they deducted the number from the monthly immigration quota.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a certain number of people that were allowed to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If illegal came, they deducted the-- you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But nobody was deported.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we figured the same thing was going to happen to us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But not this time, apparently.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What they-- what they said-- the British said, look, there is no space in the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have to go on this other ship.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it-- you will be transshipped from-- because you can't stay on this terrible ship.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's all over crowded and all that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So always 200 people are supposed to get their things together and you will be transshipped from your ship to this big ship which was-- which was standing on the other side of the port.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The ship is called the Patria, a French passenger liner which was confiscated by the British and used as a-- as a transport.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
